# Fake Error Message Prank  
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
This Batch File script displays a **custom error message** in a pop-up window to prank users.  
It uses the `msg` command to send a message to the screen, simulating a fake system warning or error.  
This is a harmless and fun way to **fool your friends or coworkers** for a laugh. üòÑ  
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  

# STEPS  
1. Open Notepad  
2. Copy and Paste the Following Code  
3. Save the File as a Batch File (`error_prank.bat`)  
4. Run `error_prank.bat`  
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  

# CODE  
@echo off  
title System Alert  
cls  

echo ===================================  
echo       FAKE ERROR MESSAGE PRANK  
echo ===================================  
echo Displaying fake system message...  
echo.  

msg * "‚ö† System Error: Critical update failed. Please restart your PC immediately!"  

echo Message sent successfully!  
echo ===================================  
pause  
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  

# Usage Tips  
1. Run `error_prank.bat`.  
2. A pop-up window will appear with the **custom error message**.  
3. You can modify the message inside the `msg *` line to anything you want.  
4. Useful for funny pranks ‚Äì just make sure it's all in good fun! üòÅ  
5. Press any key to exit after the message is displayed.  

